history.content: As these are hosted by the College of L&S, you would have to ask them. I don't expect them to change much, as their major override was for this academic year, but we'll see.

On the sites detailing which upper div humanities count towards the EECS degree requirements (https://ls.berkeley.edu/seven-course-breadth-social-and-behavioral-sciences), it says at the bottom to look at "Master List of Course Options for Social and Behavioral Sciences Effecitve Spring 2017", However there are only lists for pre Fall 2016, and Spring / Summer 2017. Where can we find updated lists effective for upcoming semesters?

Specifically was wondering about Econ c110.
